main event: Two unidentified objects were observed moving from South to North in Oakwood, Ohio for 5 minutes on August 25, 1965.
interesting points: The objects appeared brighter than a star during the observation,The flight of the objects was described as steady with no erratic movements,The observation lasted for 5 minutes without any reports of the objects disappearing,The sighting was conducted at 23:10 with a slight observer sighting noted,There were no photographs or physical evidence associated with the sighting.
